What are these import statement errors and why are they happening

# response

The import statement errors in your App.tsx are happening because you have two sets of import statements and function declarations in the same file, which is invalid JavaScript/TypeScript syntax.

Specifically:

You have import statements (e.g., import { useState } from 'react') at the top.
Then you start a function App() { ... } and inside that function, you have another set of import statements (import { BrowserRouter as Router, ... } from 'react-router-dom'; etc.), followed by another function declaration for App.
Why is this a problem?

All import statements must be at the top level of the file, not inside a function or block.
You cannot declare a function inside another function with the same name.
You have two export default App; statements, which is also invalid.
How to fix:

Remove all import statements from inside the function.
Only have one function App and one export default App.
All imports should be at the very top of the file, before any code.
